place.name: GREAT WITCHINGHAM
place.gazetteerText: WITCHINGHAM (Great), a parish, with a village, in St. Faith district, Norfolk; 7½ miles E by S of Elmham r. station. It has a post-office under Norwich. Acres, 2,245. Real property, £4,707. Pop., 642. Houses, 138. W. Halland much of the land belong to H. K. Tompson, Esq. The living is a vicarage united with Little W., in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £495.* Patron, New College, Oxford. The church is ancient, but good. There are a national school, and charities £33. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
